The paper deals with the transmission of information over a Gaussian multiple access channel (MAC) with the use of variable-length feedback codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of expected power constraints, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of feedback in communication networks is also a topic in networking (cs.NI). Finally, the paper uses tools from renewal theory, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
